### Step 2: Identify Final Accounts Payable
The final accounts payable is the sum of all unpaid purchase transactions at the end of the period. Since no new unpaid purchases are recorded during the period (all purchases are either paid or initial unpaid), the final accounts payable is the same as the initial accounts payable.
